BillTitle: An Act to amend the Criminal Code (criminal procedure, language of the accused, sentencing and other amendments)
Information:
46. Sections 7, 8, 18 to 21.1, 29, 35, 37 to 40, 42 and 44 come into force on a day or days to be fixed by order of the Governor in Council.




Her Excellency the Governor General in Council hereby fixes October 1, 2008 as the day on which sections 7, 8, 18 to 21.1, 29, 35, 37 to 40, 42 and 44 of that Act come into force.


SI/2008-0071
LegisInfoNotes: Pursuant to Order made by the House of Commons on October 25, 2007, the Bill was deemed approved at all stages completed in the previous session (previously Bill C-23 in the 1st Session of the 39th Parliament).
Committee: Standing Senate Committee on Legal and Constitutional Affairs

votes.ConstituencyName: West Vancouver—Sunshine Coast—Sea to Sky Country
